parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Master Cylinder and Brake Booster Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder and brake booster can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a loss of braking functionality, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake system warning light comes on
the brake pedal pressure gets lighter with each press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle decelerates independently
loud sounds are emitted while depressing the brake pedal
the brake fluid warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission molded lead frame can cause the transmission to inadvertently downshift, leading to loss of vehicle control, and potentially causing accidents. The speedometer may also malfunction, displaying incorrect or zero readings, which can further compromise the driver's ability to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The transmission downshifts unexpectedly
the speedometer gauge drops to zero
the service wrench warning light is displayed
the vehicle may experience sudden and unexpected loss of power
and the driver may struggle to maintain directional control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected downshifting, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents. The speedometer may also malfunction, displaying incorrect or zero readings, which can further compromise the driver's ability to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The transmission downshifts unexpectedly
the speedometer gauge drops to zero
the service wrench warning light is displayed
the vehicle may experience sudden and unexpected loss of power
and the driver may struggle to maintain directional control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the throttle body can cause intermittent loss of power, stalling, and sudden shutdown of the engine, which can lead to accidents, especially on high-speed roads, and pose a significant risk to the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Momentary losses of engine power
frequent stalling
engine shutdown with no power when pressing the accelerator
no warning lights
and powertrain fault messages on the display.
